{"format": "tiptap/v1", "updatedAt": "2026-06-22T03:58:43.947Z", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Cluster Evaluation"}, {"type": "text", "text": " is the process of assessing the quality of clusters in unsupervised learning when "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "no ground truth labels exist"}, {"type": "text", "text": " — it uses internal metrics that analyze data's natural structure to measure how tightly grouped points are within clusters and how well-separated different clusters are from each other."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What It Is"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Cluster evaluation assesses "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "clustering quality"}, {"type": "text", "text": " without true labels:"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Problem"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Unsupervised learning has no predicted labels to measure accuracy"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Solution"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Use "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "internal validation metrics"}, {"type": "text", "text": " that analyze data's natural patterns"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Focus"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Measure "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "cohesion"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (within-cluster) and "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "separation"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (between-cluster)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Key insight"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": No single metric is perfect — combining multiple metrics and visual checks gives a clearer picture of clustering performance."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why It Matters"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Challenge"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Solution"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "No ground truth labels"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use internal validation metrics that analyze data structure"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Unknown if clusters are meaningful"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Statistical tests confirm if clusters differ significantly in target variables"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Multiple algorithms/metrics"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Compare using various evaluation methods"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Business alignment"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Align clusters with problem-specific goals through validation"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Bridge to business value"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Clustering evaluation bridges gap between technical outputs and business value — without rigorous validation, clusters may appear plausible but fail to drive decisions."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key Evaluation Metrics"}]}, {"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "Cluster Evaluation — concept overview"}}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "1. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Within Cluster Sum of Squares (WCSS)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Measures"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Squared average distance of all points within a cluster to the cluster centroid"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Formula"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n$$WCSS = \\frac{1}{n_c} \\sum"}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": "{i=1}^{n_c} ||x_i - c||^2$$"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Where:\n- "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "n_c"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " = number of points in cluster\n- "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "x_i"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " = data point\n- "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "c"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " = cluster centroid"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Interpretation"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Small WCSS"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Cluster is compact (low variability)\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Large WCSS"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Cluster has greater variability (less compact)"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "When to Use"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Not Ideal When"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Assessing "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "cluster compactness"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Comparing clusters with different sizes (influenced by number of observations)"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Note"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": WCSS is often not directly comparable across clusters with different numbers of observations."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "2. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Between Clusters Sum of Squares (BCSS)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Measures"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Squared average distance between all centroids"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Formula"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n$$BCSS = \\sum"}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": "{i=1}^{k} \\sum"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{j=1}^{k} ||c_i - c_j||^2$$"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Where:\n- "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "k"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " = number of clusters\n- "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "c_i, c_j"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " = cluster centroids"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Interpretation"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Large BCSS"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Clusters are spread out (well-separated)\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Small BCSS"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Clusters are close to each other (poor separation)"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "3. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Silhouette Score (Coefficient)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Most popular metric"}, {"type": "text", "text": " — measures how similar a point is to its own cluster vs. other clusters."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Formula"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n$$s(i) = \\frac{y(i) - x(i)}{\\max(x(i), y(i))}$$"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Where:\n- "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "x(i)"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " = Average distance from point "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "i"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " to others in its cluster (intra-cluster distance)\n- "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "y(i)"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " = Average distance from point "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "i"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " to points in other clusters (inter-cluster distance)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Overall score"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Average of all points' silhouette scores"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Range"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": -1 to +1\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Close to +1"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Points nicely grouped and far from other groups\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Close to 0"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Points on cluster boundary\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Close to -1"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Points mixed up or overlapping"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Interpretation"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "High score"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (close to 1): Well-defined, separated clusters\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Low score"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (close to -1): Poor clustering, overlapping clusters"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "When to Use"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Not Ideal When"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "General clustering quality"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Very complex cluster shapes"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Scikit-learn"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "silhouette_score()"}, {"type": "text", "text": " function computes mean Silhouette Coefficient of all samples."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "4. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Davies-Bouldin Index"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Measures"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Average similarity between each cluster and its most similar neighbor"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Formula"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n$$DB = \\frac{1}{k} \\sum"}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": "{i=1}^{k} \\max"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{j \\neq i} \\left( \\frac{S_i + S_j}{M"}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": "{ij}} \\right)$$"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Where:\n- "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "S_i"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " = Average distance of points in cluster "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "i"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " to centroid (within-cluster)\n- "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "M_{ij}"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " = Distance between centroids of clusters "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "i"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " and "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "j"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " (between-cluster)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Interpretation"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Lower scores"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Clusters are compact and well-separated ("}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "better"}, {"type": "text", "text": ")\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Higher scores"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Clusters overlap or are poorly separated ("}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "worse"}, {"type": "text", "text": ")"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "When to Use"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Not Ideal When"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Assessing "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "compactness + separation"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": " "}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Key insight"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Looks at how similar each cluster is to its most similar neighbor."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "5. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Calinski-Harabasz (CH) Index"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Also called"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Variance Ratio Criterion"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Measures"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Ratio of between-cluster variance to within-cluster variance"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Formula"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n$$CH = \\frac{BCSS / (k - 1)}{WCSS / (n - k)}$$"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Where:\n- "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "BCSS"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " = Between Clusters Sum of Squares\n- "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "WCSS"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " = Within Cluster Sum of Squares\n- "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "k"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " = number of clusters\n- "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "n"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " = total number of points"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Interpretation"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Higher values"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Better-defined clusters with higher separation and lower dispersion ("}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "better"}, {"type": "text", "text": ")\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Lower values"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Poorly separated clusters ("}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "worse"}, {"type": "text", "text": ")"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Key insight"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Checks how much clusters differ from each other compared to how spread out points are within each cluster."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "6. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Average Distance from Centroid"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Measures"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Average distance of points to their cluster centroid"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Used for"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Comparing within-cluster variabilities of different clusters (better than WCSS for this)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Interpretation"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Small distance"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Compact cluster\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Large distance"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Less compact cluster"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Choosing Optimal K for k-Means"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Method"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How It Works"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {